cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is about face image super-resolution using a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of adversarial training, which is a common technique in deep learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also involves image processing, so cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category. The use of embedding vectors and feature fusion suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper involves image alignment, which is a common problem in computer graphics, so cs.GR (Computer Graphics) is a less likely but still possible category.
